tom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:10.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Calibri\",\"sans-serif\";}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(8, 82, 148);\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">PRE COMMISSIONING AND COMMISSIONING\r\nSERVICES</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(57, 132, 198);\"><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Pre\r\nCommissioning</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Pre Commissioning, also referred to as\r\nstatic commissioning, starts when a system or subsystem achieves Mechanical\r\nCompletion. The safety monitoring activities will change at this transition as\r\nfluids (water, air, nitrogen, hydrocarbons, etc.) are introduced into sections\r\nof the facility to support testing, cleaning, flushing, and other\r\npre-commissioning activities. Pre-Commissioning activities are items that are\r\ndone following Mechanical Completion. Attached is a typical list of\r\nPre-Commissioning Items: </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">1. Temporary Screens, Strainers and Blinds\r\n– Doing walk down checks, witnessing </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">2. Air and Steam Blowing – Cleaning the\r\nsystems</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">3. Flushing, Chemical and Mechanical\r\nCleaning </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">4. Cleaning and Passivation – Ensure 100%\r\ncleaning</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">5. Electrical System Energizing – Essential\r\npre commissioning of equipment</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">6. Instrumentation Verification – A must of\r\ntotal system readiness for commissioning.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"color: rgb(57, 132, 198);\"><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Commissioning\r\n</span></b></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Commissioning is a verification process\r\nused to confirm that a facility has been designed, procured, fabricated,\r\ninstalled, tested, and prepared for operation in accordance with design\r\ndrawings and specifications. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Commissioning Items are: </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">1. Operational Tightness Testing </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">2. Oil Systems Flushing </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">3. Loading of desiccants/burning fuels and\r\ncatalysts </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">4. Refractory dry out 5. Run in of rotating\r\nequipment </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">6. Drying Out and inerting </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">7. Instrument and electrical function\r\ntesting </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">8. Function testing of safety systems</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">9. Function testing of installed equipment\r\nto its full capacity.</span></p>\r\n\r\n', '', 1566411420, 2, -1),
